ard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=21&stop=24>2</a> </td><td align=right> <br> <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=142.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=142.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top background=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/tableBackground.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/tableBackground.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirfurismerud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Furism Erud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/14/02 4:28:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> Hello,<br><br>I was wondering if with Divine Intervention Act of Valor could be 'survived' - which is still valorous - or if that kind of spells don't apply ? <p><table width="294" border="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.factornews.com/furism/furism.gif" width="25" height="44" border="0"></a></td><td valign="top"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8" target="_blank">Furism</a><br>Deepwater Crusader of Prexus<br><a href="http://novae.dhs.org/forum/" target="_blank">Novae</A> - Karana</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueiago.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiago</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 238<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/14/02 10:19:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> You fall to your death when you do it, so I would expect they 10k you.<br><br><br> <p><b>Eiago X'ul Octavious <br>Tunare's Crusader<br></b><a href="http://innercircle.frags.ws">Inner Circle</a> <br> <b>Xegony</b><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77152 ">Profile</a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 1270<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 7:23:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> There are types of death that are unsavable.  That is even with Divine Intervention on it will never check to see if it is triggered.  I believe things like Death Touch, falling, and Act of Valor fall into this category.<br><br>IMHO, Act of Valor is just plain worthless.  There are almost no situations where another 4k of hit points and you dying is going to help(and I'm being generous about the 4k part).<br><br>ps. whether this is actually coded or side effect enforced is up in the air.  no one sane is willing to test this over and over to find out. ^_^ <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usirfurismerud.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Furism Erud</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 7:39:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> Hmm throwing 6k HP (a well equiped Paladin with lots of base STA and Durability 3 can get that high) is pretty good to heal a MT at the very beginning of a fight (like AoW) without generating any aggro (since you're dead :) I'm my humble opinion.<br><br>Thanks for the info :) <p><table width="294" border="0"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.factornews.com/furism/furism.gif" width="25" height="44" border="0"></a></td><td valign="top"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8" target="_blank">Furism</a><br>Deepwater Crusader of Prexus<br><a href="http://novae.dhs.org/forum/" target="_blank">Novae</A> - Karana</font></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulallailwhytefyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lallail Whytefyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 103<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 9:22:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> For all the time and effort you put into getting Act of Valor, you could easily keep yourself equiped with a charged soulfire for the rest of your gaming career to use as the first CH on a MT during a raid.  He gets back just as much if not more hp, and you get to live and contribute additional healing even if you do pull agro and have to DA the mob back onto the MT.<br><br>While not totally worthless, its in no way worth the time to get it vs other options, even just raising your base wis/sta etc.<br><br>Lallail Whytefyre<br>Crusader of Tunare<br>Rodcet Nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 1271<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 9:39:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> But if you die at the beginning of the fight as described in the senario, you've done *0* damage, died with a full bar of mana and only healed for 6k(not to mention wasted the mana of people who had to buff you out to 6k hit points).  You can do that with Improved Lay Hands **by itself** let alone the 6k+ you can heal with just your mana alone and still be able to melee!<br><br>Dying for one heal is such a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  huge</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> waste especially at the beginning of the fight. <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/15/02 9:40:59 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 9:44:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> Act of Valor is amazing.<br><br>Besides its utility in raids (OOM, no loh, tank/dam-dealer about to drop) it has a huge 'fun' factor.<br><br>Standing in the bank, you see someone you know with low hps...<br><br>&quot;Lemme top you off there Soandso!&quot;<br>*BOOM*<br>&lt;hilarity ensues&gt;<br><br>Or, perhaps you see a particularly snuggly gnome stroll by...<br><br>&quot;)@*#)!(@*$)(!@ YOU ARE SO SNUGGLY LET ME TOP YOU OFF@(*#!@&quot;<br>*BOOM*<br>&lt;hilarity and snuggling ensues&gt;<br><br>Hell, one time I was running through the dreadlands and hit it just to see it go off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>At level 60 who gives a shit about experience? Being a walking death touch owns you<br><br>Xarn Yum Chai<br>&quot;King of the Unnecessary Death Touch&quot;<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aeka>Aeka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 1272<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 9:52:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> Xarn has an excellent point!  I mean people only snicker when you accidently /disc resistent at the bank but nothing gets people to poke fun like falling over dead. ^_^ <p><font size="+1">Aeka<br>Level 60 Paladin on Povar<br><font color="#cc00cc">Just don't ask about the purple hair</font></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 313<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 12:24:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> I accidentally used Resistant the other day before a Vox raid, just before my group went in to start killing some of the giants. If I had used AoV (which I don't have BTW) I would have killed myself. ^_^ <p><font><font size=3><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45984>Balidin</a>,</font> The Evilbasher</b><BR><font color=red><i>Cavalier of Mithaniel</i><BR><font color=white>Apprentice of the Healing Arts of Rodcet Nife</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwulf9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulf9</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 1:23:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> I just knew overexposure to Gnomes would do bad things to a persons sanity ;/ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualphawolfsilverblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alphawolf Silverblood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/15/02 1:47:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> I have to agree with the majority of posts here.  Using a soulfire is more beneficial to the MT than using AoV.  I could see this having some use if it didn't completely kill you or perhaps if it were like necro's lifeburn or maybe the discipline that I can recall being recommended on this board before.  The paladin uses this discipline and a split is created of the dmg being incurred by the target to go part way to the subject of the discipline and part way to the paladin using it.  Using this to heal is quite simply a waste however, I must agree.  For an example fighting the Avatar of War as previously mentioned, if you used this at the beginning of the fight you would be making inefficient use of resources that would otherwise be useful in dmg'ing the target and reducing the time taken for the fight.  This has two sides: one, the target is not doing damage for the extended period of time that he/she would otherwise be dead because of damage you *could* have done; two, it is less mana that must be used in order to heal the main tank (if that is your strategy) instead of using your own life in order to heal the MT.<br><br>Alphawolf Silverblood<br>Crusader of Clan Ta'Veren<br>Terris Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 1001<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 10:54:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> So basically it's useful on a slim few very very high end encounters and for dying at the bank.<br>I think I'd rather spend the aa points on +str then aov. <br><br>The risk/reward factor seems very poor on this one.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 11:11:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> I will chime in that during the melee class balance talks, this was one of the things Paladins asked for.  Verant gave us what we asked for, in the form of an AA ability.  Many of the other AA abilities were on the same list. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 1002<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 11:34:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> This wasn't really what I had imagined it to be.<br>We were looking at something more along the lines of sharing hp rather than instant death if I recall correctly.<br>Something like 50% of the damage taken by the warrior was offset by the paladins own hitpoints. It's probably very difficult to implement something like this, but I don't think aov in it's current form was what people were looking for.  <br><br>Or at least add your hp to the warriors total hp like a rune so it would give that warrior 10k hp to start off a battle. <br>Death for an instant CH isn't that attractive, when we already have the ability to instantly CH without causing death. <br><br>It's situational at best and unless you are in the position where you are doing very high end encounters and for some reason major healing at crucial intervals is required it's not worth the aa points. I realize that alot of people are starting to get to the tougher content, but it's still a bottom of the list ability compared to the value gained from picking other skills.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 12:51:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> Yes that was also recommended Bizomb.  I don't have copies of the first Paladin Talk thread, but I know I read some suggestions right along the lines of what Act of Valor is.  I saved many of the pages from the second thread to my hard drive (the first one got corrupted so it was deleted before I could save it), here are some of the suggestions along these lines:<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>I really like the idea of paladin protecting another person. <br>While i would like a copy of defensive, this new discipline in place of holyforge (you really need to put crit/crip on undead always running...) would greatly help Paladins on large raids or even normal groups, and is unique to us. <br><br>Let's base it on defensive. It works during 3 minutes and can recharge every 10 minutes at 60 and during the period of 3 minutes, the paladin will take on him half the damage of his target. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>9) &quot;Sacrifice&quot; discipline/skill<br>At level 55 or so, allow paladins, when this discipline/skill is activated, to kill themselves and Complete Heal the group. Exp would be lost as if it was an evironmental or monster-inflicted death. This would still CH the group even if the paladin was down to 5 HP when he activated it. Obviously, even with the 96% cleric rez, a death at that level is a nice setback. The exp loss would certainly keep people from using this very often...And yes, the paladin should be rez-able if he uses this. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>3. A new spell/discipline. We need a new spell/discipline that allows us to redirect damage at one party member to ourselves. Being the noble knights we are, we should be able to sacrifice ourselves to save another. There is potential for misuse so I would suggest that this is a discipline and not a spell, and that our ability to sacrifice increases with levels. The ability is gained at 50th level with 50% damage transferal and 2% for each level thereafter. This should have a high taunt factor associated with it. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>In addition to LoH, paladins should have a discipline to supplement this purpose. Some here have suggested a Holy Defender discipline, where the paladin can forgo damage dealing to defend hits against another party member. <br><br>As my suggestion, please give us an ability to move us up to the TOP of the hate list for a particular mob. On rare occasions, we should be able to pull something onto us without question. Could this be unbalancing? Yes, if a paladin could easily survive such a fight. If a paladin uses this ability, he should lose LoH if it is up. The mob's damage onto him should also be increased. Basically, this discipline would allow a Paladin to die to save the rest of his party. <br><br>I think that this could even work together with a Holy Defender-type discipline. A battle is going very badly, so a Paladin uses LoH on himself. He then uses this discipline to pull the mob onto him. Then he uses his Holy Defender discipline to not fight in return for better blocks and parries. The mob still hits him for tremendous damage, and he dies 25-30 seconds later, long enough for the rest of the party to escape. <br><br>There would be many paladins that would be too selfish to use this discipline, so those of us that would would become rather valuable.<br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>13) Give Paladins a 'let me take your damage for you' type spell/skill... mostly for the intent of high level raids... basically put it on someone, and all the damage they take is deferred to you, instead of them taking it. It kind of fits in with the 'sacrifice for the life of friends' roleplaying aspect of Paladins. I agree wit this one. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>&gt;&quot;I propose that we get a ability by means of a spell that would allow us to protect a target from harm by the paladin taking it in the targets place. I have heard this numerous times and I think it is our only shot at getting a better slot in the high level raids.&quot;&lt; <br><br>Yes, a very popular idea. I'll add it to the list. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>That &quot;Yes, a very popular idea. I'll add it to the list.&quot; line was from Absor, the Verant customer relations guy reading the posts.<br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>New discipline &quot;Martyr&quot; - Group LOH, paladin dies (xp loss to avoid abuse). <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>1. Allow paladins to absorb damage directed at another. <br><br>2. Allow paladins to sacrifice themselves by dying but heal the other members of the party. <br><br>3. Allow paladins some defensive-like discipline appropriate for the defensive tanks we are (such as the holy shield discipline I proposed). <br><br>Whatever option you choose, paladins should get it at 55 so that we can participate in raids. Please relook and reconsider your position on this issue. It is the most important enhancement that we can receive and the one most desperately needed. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>I don't play a paladin but i think it would be neat if a paladin could sacrifice himself to save his group. sorta like a group complete heal and the paladin dies and cannot get his exp back through a res. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>1 - Spell level 54 : Blood sacrifice - cast time 2 sec - Remove 500hp to yourself to give to you target. (if you use it too much, well you die) <br><br>I would see this spell so usefull in any fight we do.. ench get beat down, cleric is low HP... often when we are with warrior, or other tanks, we dont get hit in a fight... I would see if that ench is i trouble, you hurt yourself to heal him.. thats would be very efficient. <br><br>2 - Discipline : /protection - Take 30% of all the group damage (yeah AE dragon could kill you in 1 kill, but i see that one good in many situation too) <br><br>3 - Discipline : /sacrifice - Kill yourself, group CH - I can see some paladin invite in raid... Dragon is low. cleric is out of mana, everyone is about to die... paladins kill themself to give groups a 15 more sec to finish the ubermob. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>One - At whatever level you deem appropriate, add a discipline that is a gaurenteed taunt and keeps you number one on the mob's aggro list for a pre-determined length of time or until you or it are dead. In the latter case give it a healthy refresh rate. This will allow the Paladin to do the ole jump in front of the mob to save a party member's life by giving his own. <br><br>Two - Give us a spell, again at appropriate level you determine, that casts a Rune like spell on the recipiant, but rather than the damage just vanishing, it is transfered to the Paladin. So the mob smacks Bob Wizard for 75 points but the message reads, &quot;blow is deflected at Joe Paladin for 75 points&quot; <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>There was suggestion about a discipline that would be the perfect way to reflect the Paladin's role as a defender. That was the possibility of allowing the Paladin to absorb the damage meant for a party member. Targeting that group member to acitvate the effect would nulify the Paladin's ability to do damage, but from that point on, they would be sacrificing thier own body in the stead of another's. Allowing this damage abosorbtion shouldn't cause significant balance issues. The damage is still being dealt. It is just being re-directed. This disc could easily be the heroic move that saves the day, when used to protect the enchanter who is absolutely essential to restoring order, or the sole cleric from whom the only source of heals is a necessity. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>I love the idea of a spell/discipline that would allow me to divert damage from one player onto myself. If you implemented this idea I think you would satisfy 90% of the concerns of a vast majority of the paladin community. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  <br>Sacrifice - I have seen this posted. I would like to share an idea for implementation. <br><br>This ability could work like this: <br><br>1. Paladin dies<br>2. Group gets 20 seconds of invulnerablity (Message could read: Diety XXX acknowleges Paladin XXX's sacrifice) <br><br>This is a neat idea and also is neat for the role players. <br><hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A> at: 4/16/02 12:53:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 1004<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 5:18:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Act of Valor pwns</span><hr size=1> None of the definitions you have listed are what aov is in it's current implementation. They either are damage supplements or rune style things or a sacrifice but the amount healed isn't dependant on your current hp and the amount generally is group heal not individual.<br><br>Verant took all the bad ideas out of the suggestions and made aov. <br>Instead of group healing, it's a single individual. You have to have hp to give hp so it's not like you can sacrifice yourself to heal another if you've taken serious damage. It's a one shot deal whereas most are suggesting a damage sharing or a over time hp swap as opposed to this here's my hp now I'm dead version.<br><br>It's a bad implementation of suggestions from the board if you ask me. In it's current form it's is way too situational and even then if you are in a situation where the single heal from a paladin is going to make or break your raid, I'd suggest getting another cleric.<br><br>Until I have very few options left I'm not wasting aa points on aov. I'd probably go with the abundant food and drink one as opposed to aov. <br><br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ucaladel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 415<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/16/02 7:55:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=16>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> /agree<br><br>The prevelant ideas in that thread were 1) death to the paladin in return for a group ch or group heal, and 2) a feel your pain skill/spell that shares target damage.<br><br>Either i would still like btw, if AoV was a group CH i would get the skill, but till its upgraded its at the very end of the list.<br><br>A group ch, or an ae heal would be fine for the skill. An ae heal on the order of about 1000 would be fine. Note clerics already get an ae heal of 1150 with mass group buff and casting blessing of ageolism, as do shamans a 430hp ae heal with mass group buff and casting Khura's Focusing. So, a 1000 ae heal instant for a paladin would not be unbalancing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 133<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 6:43:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> I'm not arguing with you Bizomb or Caladel.  I do remember distinctly that at least a few people posted more specifically the AoV idea in the first Paladin Talk thread, but it was corrupted before I saved it, so I can't quote those.<br><br>What you see here is the second thread, where people were posting variations on that theme.<br><br>I'm also not arguing with you that AoV has limited usefulness at best.  I think it's hard enough to make optimal use out of LoH in a raid situation, much less a 2nd LoH where you have to weigh in the downside of taking yourself out of the fight.<br><br>Someone did ask for it though, I remember a post where they said they'd like a Paladin to be able to &quot;fall on their sword&quot; and give their hit points to someone else.<br><br>Also, with the current implementation of HWoP, we basically got a group LoH/CH (over time) without even needing to die, it's a mana drain instead. <p><BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Aalek</a><BR>60 Crusader<BR>Reign in Power<BR>Torvonnilous</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A> at: 4/17/02 6:44:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugraalthedorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Graal the Dorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 221<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/02 11:45:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> Question....is AoV tied to the LoH timer? If it is, it is a completely worthless skill. If not, it would have it's uses. <p><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686"> Graal MacBladefury</A><BR>59 Knight of Brell<BR>Champions of Norrath<BR>The Rathe<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 1016<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/18/02 8:46:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV ?</span><hr size=1> I'm pretty sure they are on separate timers.<br>So you are correct that it gives an additional insta CH for the paladin. However when you are talking about risk vs reward it is way too situational and costly to use this except for extremely rare circumstances. Assist heals and CH rotations and things make an additional spot heal really unnecessary. Particularly when that single spot heal sacrifices 1500+ damage a minute and all other paladin stun/taunt/healing wave/etc abilities.<br><br>It'd be a better idea to farm soulfire and have the CH on that saved up for your tank than to spend the aa points on this. There were people who said they wanted to fall on thier sword for another. I wasn't one of em. hehe. I was in the damage sharing boat which would provide a lot more versatility and use than aov in it's current form.<br><br>We have several very nice skills in our class abilities so I'll focus on those. This is just one I won't bother getting the skill for unless someone can show me a real need for it. Which I haven't really seen yet.<br><br>Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualphawolfsilverblood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alphawolf Silverblood</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/18/02 9:14:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=142.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Surviving AoV?</span><hr size=1> All I have to say is that I completely agree with Bizomb and I too were in support of the damage splitting idea but Act of Valor is just a misused attempt of the majority's ideas.<br><br>Alphawolf Silverblood <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm13.showMessageRange?topicID=142.topic&start=21&stop=24>2</